            <fieldText>&lt;p&gt;A customer’s mobile is also their authentication to access the portal and can be used to reset their password. It’s important we ensure any requests to change a mobile are legitimate and have come from the client. By clicking next, you confirm that:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;For a request received from the client over email, the partner has called the customer to confirm the client made this request - this is mandatory because emails can easily be hacked and we cannot trust an email alone&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;For a request received over the phone, you have asked the customer to provide 2 pieces of information that we hold on them - this is to ensure it’s not just someone else calling and claiming to be them&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;We are not updating the mobile for someone other than the person who made the request&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</fieldText>
